    15	intermediate knowledge representation is *ontologically consistent* — i.e. that
    16	the encoded triples satisfy the class hierarchy and method signatures defined in
    17	the ontology.  Inconsistencies are reported alongside the cosine similarity
    18	score so that callers can decide how to handle them.
    19	
    20	Example::
    21	
